<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1940-03-25T12:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1940-03-25T12:00:00-05:00" n="770" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d770">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">862.857/148: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in the Dominican Republic</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Hinkle</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Ciudad Trujillo</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-03-25T12:00:00-05:00">March 25,
                                    1940—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received 1:28 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>53. Department’s 31, March 21, 5 p.m. Dominican Foreign Secretary states
                            that he is today telegraphing Dr. Garay his Government’s approval of the
                            drafts and procedure.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Hinkle</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>